-- South Africa Formally Asked to Join as BRIC Country Member, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 2010-12-24T07:53:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-24/south-africa-formally-asked-to-join-bric-group-as-member-xinhua-reports.html
South Africa has been formally asked
to join the BRIC group, which includes Brazil, Russia, India and
China, Xinhua reported, citing Chinese Foreign Minister Yang
Jiechi.  Yang spoke to South African Foreign Minister Maite Nkoana-
Mashabane by phone and a formal letter of invitation will be
sent to President Jacob Zuma to invite him to a BRIC head of
state summit in Beijing next year, the news agency said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  